Discussing core issues here is fine, within reason.  By this I mean
that the issues should not be restricted to those of a single mud.

I've become somewhat disillusioned with frobs as a means of applying
OO concepts to the language, and I think operator overloading is just
going to confuse things.  I'm planning to rethink altogether the way
Coldmud deals with types.

--GBH

